<common-name datatype='string'>rybB</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>The expression of the &lt;i&gt;rybB&lt;/i&gt; gene is enhanced during the transition from the exponential to the stationary phase [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17007876&quot;&gt;Johansen06&lt;/a&gt;], but this induction is RpoS independent  [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17416652&quot;&gt;Thompson07&lt;/a&gt;]. 
&lt;p&gt;
The NsrR transcriptional repressor regulates negatively the transcription of the &lt;i&gt;rybB&lt;/i&gt; gene, but it is not known if this effect is direct or indirect [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17416652&quot;&gt;Thompson07&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;

The RNA produced by the &lt;i&gt;rybB&lt;/i&gt; gene has been observed mainly in the poles of the cell during  stress conditions [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/31540875&quot;&gt;Kannaiah19&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
